<p>This comes after Jessica said she wants her company to 'value' areas including 'health, wellness, and stability'.</p>

<p>The actress is the co-founder of consumer goods company The Honest Company, and has said she's determined for the brand to put 'honesty and transparency' first, because she believes customers expect brands to have those values 'embedded into the model'.</p>

<p>'I think if we can do anything for business, we can show that you could have a positive impact on the world, you can put health and wellness and sustainability as a value, you can have honesty and transparency as a value,' she said.</p>

